topic: Companies Workflow Series ("IT Companies explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for obtaining number of employees of a company and other relevant numerical attributes
goals.2: Identify the BGP to retrieve all companies owned by a company
goals.3: Is there some company that owns companies in other countries?
goals.4: Companies have different 'legal forms', compare the number of companies divided in different legal forms
goals.5: Analyze the number of employees  and other relevant numeric attributes
goals.5.1: What are the top-10 companies for a given attribute?
goals.5.2: For which companies is defined some form of income or market capitalization or total assets? What is the min, max, and average in each category and country?
goals.5.3: Which business in each country owns more businesses in other countries?

search_workflow.narrative:
let's try and filter the properties by name, we're looking for keywords such as number of employees, revenue, capital, assets
sector, if a company owns or is onwned by some other company, the ceo...
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?propertyName where{{ ?b wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 . ?b ?property ?predicate . ?b wdt:P17 ?country . filter(?country in (wd:Q16, wd:Q145, wd:Q30)) . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?propertyName . filter regex(?propertyName, '.*(employee|revenue|capital|asset|owne|ceo|c.e.o.|sector).*' ,'i') . }}
output: category for employees of the organization
execution_output: category for employees of the organization

search_workflow.narrative:
let's define for now variables for the properties we care about
we couldn't find a property related to sector, let's try with a company we know, for example Microsoft, and see its properties
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?companyName ?property ?propertyName where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?companyName ; wdt:P17 wd:Q30 ; ?property ?o . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?propertyName . filter regex(?companyName, 'microsoft', 'i') }}
output: Union List of Artist Names ID
The Times of India topic ID
execution_output: Union List of Artist Names ID
The Times of India topic ID

search_workflow.narrative:
with a more readable output, we're able to find out the properties related to the CEO and the "product or material produced"
i forgot to show the company uri, i have to filter by name of the company again
let's find out the ceo and the product of microsoft
search_workflow.query: select ?company, ?companyName, ?ceoName, ?product, ?productName where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q30 ; wdt:P169 ?ceo ; wdt:P1056 ?product ; <http://schema.org/name> ?companyName . ?ceo <http://schema.org/name> ?ceoName . ?product <http://schema.org/name> ?productName . filter regex(?companyName, 'microsoft', 'i') }}

search_workflow.narrative:
there is one product, "computer hardware", that may help us find the class related to products of a company, the other results are just the name of specific products
let's find the class of "computer hardware"
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?className where{{ wd:Q3966 wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's do that again for "electronics"
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?className where{{ wd:Q11650 wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }}

search_workflow.narrative: this is bringing us nowhere, maybe "computer hardware" is subclass of something more general
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?super ?name where{{ wd:Q3966 wdt:P279 ?super . ?super <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's try to fetch american companies and their products
search_workflow.query: select ?companyName ?productName where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 ; wdt:P1056 ?product ; <http://schema.org/name> ?companyName ; wdt:P17 wd:Q30 . ?product wdt:P279 wd:Q2424752 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?productName . }} order by asc(?productName) limit 20

search_workflow.narrative:
with the more general product class that we found, does microsoft produce software as well?
let's get microsoft's uri
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?company ?companyName where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453; <http://schema.org/name> ?companyName . filter regex(?companyName, 'microsoft', 'i') }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's see all products of microsoft
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?product ?productName where{{ wd:Q2283 wdt:P1056 ?product . ?product wdt:P279 wd:Q2424752 . ?product <http://schema.org/name> ?productName }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's check visual studio's class and superclass
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?className ?superClass ?superClassName where{{ wd:Q134067 wdt:P31 ?class . wd:Q134067 wdt:P279 ?superClass . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . ?superClass <http://schema.org/name> ?superClassName . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's add optionals
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?className ?superClass ?superClassName where{{ wd:Q134067 wdt:P31 ?class . optional{{ wd:Q134067 wdt:P279 ?superClass . ?superClass <http://schema.org/name> ?superClassName . }} ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
this didn't help us either. the only thing i can think of is to go back to the list of properties for microsoft and search for another one
doing this i found the property "industry", let's check that out
let's see the industry for some companies in the us
search_workflow.query: select ?companyName ?industry ?industryName where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q30 ; wdt:P452 ?industry ; <http://schema.org/name> ?companyName . ?industry <http://schema.org/name> ?industryName }} limit 20

search_workflow.narrative: let's count the number of companies in the us for each industry
search_workflow.query: select ?industry ?industryName (count(*) as ?total) where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 ; wdt:P452 ?industry ; wdt:P17 wd:Q30 . ?industry <http://schema.org/name> ?industryName . }} group by ?industry ?industryName limit 30
execution_output: Insurance, reinsurance and pension funding, except compulsory social security

search_workflow.narrative:
let's start answering to the goals using all the properties found earlier
point 1 is already complete since we know all the relevant properties. Let's list them for some companies
employees
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?companyName ?employees where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?companyName ; wdt:P1128 ?employees . }} limit 20

search_workflow.narrative: assets and revenue
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?companyName ?assets ?revenue where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?companyName ; wdt:P2403 ?assets ; wdt:P2139 ?revenue . }} limit 20

search_workflow.narrative: combining everything
search_workflow.query: select ?company ?companyName ?n_employees ?revenue ?assets where{{ ?company wdt:P31 wd:Q4830453 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?companyName ; wdt:P1128 ?n_employees ; wdt:P2139 ?revenue ; wdt:P2403 ?assets . }} order by desc(?revenue) limit(10)
